@@mMENTAL POWER@@N

Mental Power is a stacking combat mechanic for psionic, necromancer, ego, and
kinetic spellcasters (PSI, NEC, EGO, KIN spells).

@@WBuilding the Stack:@@N
  Each time you successfully cast a PSI, NEC, EGO, or KIN spell, your Mental
  Power increases by 1. The stack persists as long as you remain in combat.
  It resets to 0 when you leave combat.

@@WBenefits:@@N
  For every point of Mental Power, the mana cost of PSI, NEC, EGO, and KIN
  spells is reduced by @@y2%@@N per stack. For example, 10 stacks grants a 20%
  mana cost reduction on those spells.

@@WRisk - Mental Overload:@@N
  Each time you cast a PSI, NEC, EGO, or KIN spell while you have Mental Power
  stacked, there is a @@r1% chance per stack@@N that your mental focus will
  shatter. If this occurs:
    - The spell does not fire.
    - Your Mental Power stack is reset to 0.
    - No mana is spent.

  At higher stacks this risk grows quickly. At 20 stacks there is a 20% chance
  of collapse on each cast, so managing your stack is crucial.

@@WPrompt Code:@@N
  Use @@y%Q@@N in your prompt to display your current Mental Power. See HELP PROMPT.
